<p>Catel-Manzke syndrome is characterized by the Pierre Robin anomaly, which comprises cleft palate, glossoptosis, and micrognathia, and a unique form of bilateral hyperphalangy in which there is an accessory bone inserted between the second metacarpal and its corresponding proximal phalanx, resulting in radial deviation of the index finger (summary by Manzke et al., 2008).</p>

<p>[Manzke, H., Lehmann, K., Klopocki, E., Caliebe, A. Catel-Manzke syndrome: two new patients and a critical review of the literature. Europ. J. Med. Genet. 51: 452-465, 2008.]<br/></p>